how i write marjorie perloff bio home writers conversation transcripts videos notes on writing sponsoring programs marjorie perloff professor emerita of english marjorie perloff writes on contemporary and avant garde poetry and poetics as well as on intermedia and the visual arts her many books include the poetics of indeterminacy rimbaud to cage the futurist moment avant garde avant guerre and the language of rupture and wittgenstein's ladder professor perloff has recently published her cultural memoir the vienna paradox which has been widely discussed she has written widely for periodicals such as tls and the washington post as well as major scholarly journals she is a member of the american academy of arts and sciences and is the current president of the modern language association wednesday may 3 2006 7 pm stanford writing center basement of margaret jacks hall bldg 460 home writers conversation transcripts videos notes on writing sponsoring programs
